Sentencas: A composite perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 carbonate (BSCF-SDCC) coating was investigated to enhance the performance of SUS 430 stainless steel as interconnect material for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: BSCF-SDCC powder was successfully obtained by low-speed wet milling method from commercial BSCF, SDC, and binary carbonates.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: The developed BSCF-SDCC powder were heat-treated 600 degrees C for 90 min, and then characterized by X-ray diffraction (XRD) and field-emission scanning electron microscopy (FESEM) equipped with energy-dispersive spectroscopy (EDS).
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: FESEM revealed better morphology of BSCF-SDCC powder with heat treatment.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: However, XRD analysis showed the destruction of BSCF phase in the BSCF-SDCC powder after heat treatment at 600 degrees C. Moreover, electrophoretic deposition (EPD) of BSCF-SDCC powder in an ethanol-added dispersing agent suspension was investigated under 10 volt 10 minutes by 10 g/l.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: The coated samples were then heat-treated at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: The coated samples were characterized by comparing between the samples with and without heat treatment based on XRD, SEM-EDS, and area specific resistance (ASR) analyses.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: XRD analysis indicated BSCF phases disappeared for the samples with heat treatment.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: The heat-treated sample performed better coating morphology and fewer pores.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: The samples underwent 500 hours of air oxidation at 600 degrees C, and ASR was measured by DC 2-point method during in situ oxidation process.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: The coated sample with heat treatment at 600 degrees C exhibited excellent low area-specific resistance reading of below 0.1 Omega cm2, which is an essential requirement for interconnect materials.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect

Sentencas: After 500 h of oxidation, the XRD patterns revealed stable phase and maintained good coating morphology.
Titulo: Effect of Heat Treatment on the Structural, Morphology and Electrochemical Performance of Perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 Carbonate Protective Coating for SOFC Metallic Interconnect
